modules.description: Provides pattern matching macros for algebraic data types, enabling concise and readable case analysis. Works with variant types and custom syntax extensions to generate efficient match coverage checks. Used to enforce exhaustive pattern matching in code that processes structured data.

Processes pattern matching expansions by transforming input patterns into expressions using a given context. Operates on OCaml parsetree patterns and expressions, leveraging extension contexts for metaprogramming. Used to generate custom match expansion logic during code transformation phases.
